description:
Refactor API routes to support multiple providers through abstraction.

## Current GitHub-Specific Routes
All in apps/www/lib/routes/github.*.route.ts:
- github.oauth-token.route.ts
- github.prs.route.ts (list, open, patch, files, file-contents, etc.)
- github.repos.route.ts
- github.install-state.route.ts

## Abstraction Strategy

### Option A: Provider Parameter in Existing Routes
```typescript
// /integrations/:provider/prs
// /integrations/:provider/repos
// Provider extracted from path parameter
```

### Option B: Unified Routes with Query Param
```typescript
// /integrations/prs?provider=github
// /integrations/repos?provider=gitlab
```

### Recommended: Option A with Shared Logic
```typescript
// apps/www/lib/routes/integrations/
//   prs.route.ts        (handles all providers)
//   repos.route.ts
//   oauth.route.ts
//   webhooks.route.ts

// Route handler
app.get('/integrations/:provider/prs', async (c) => {
  const provider = c.req.param('provider')
  const gitProvider = getGitProvider(provider)
  return gitProvider.listPullRequests(...)
})
```

